headline: This $1 Billion Trump Loan For Three Mile Island Lifts S&P 500 Nuclear Giant
summary: Constellation Energy shares angled higher before Wednesday's stock market open after the Department of Energy announced late Tuesday that the S&P 500 nuclear giant's plans to restart a Three Mile Island reactor is now backed by a $1 billion Trump administration loan.  The Department of Energy loan is expected to cover much of the project's estimated $1.6 billion cost with the first advance expected to make its way to Constellation Energy in Q1 2026.  The nuclear giant first announced it will be firing back up Pennsylvania's Three Mile Island Unit 1 in September 2024 as part of a ¬†two-decade long contract with Microsoft to provide power for the tech giant's data centers.

headline: US stocks climb ahead of a crucial couple of tests for Wall Street

It‚Äôs been shaky recently, not just day to day but also hour to hour, because of worries that stock prices have broadly shot too high and that the Federal Reserve may not deliver as many revitalizing jolts through lower interest rates as expected.

headline: Wall Street swings through another unsettled day ahead of a crucial couple of tests
summary: The U.S. stock market is swinging through another unsettled day of trading on Wednesday, as a huge couple of tests loom on Wall Street.  The S&P 500 added 0.2% after veering in the morning between virtually no gain and a jump of 1.1%.  The index is coming off a four-day losing streak, its longest in nearly three months, and has been shaky recently because of worries that stock prices have shot too high and that the Federal Reserve may not deliver as many revitalizing cuts to interest rates as expected.
